{
  "texts": [
    "This condition is likely caused by an inflammatory response due to lung infection. 4.",
    "Changes in lung density: X-ray images of pneumonia patients might reveal alterations in lung density, which could be a result of lung tissue being affected by infection or inflammation.",
    "Density changes may include lung tissue infiltration, condensation, or diffusion. 5.",
    "Pleural thickening: X-ray images of pneumonia patients may reveal pleural thickening, which refers to an increase in thickness of the pleura lining the lungs within the chest cavity.",
    "Pleural thickening is often associated with lung infection or inflammation.These distinctions observed in X-ray images provide important diagnostic information and aid in the distinction between pneumonia patients and healthy individuals.It is important to note that these differences may be relative, and the characteristic manifestations of pneumonia may vary depending on individual differences."
  ]
}